<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="901" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d901">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79600/7–545: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-05T18:00:00-04:00">July 5,
                                    1945—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>188. You may convey to Saudi authorities info in Depcirtel July 5,<note n="49" xml:id="d901fn49">
                                <ref target="frus1945v02#pg_1460">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>,
                                    p. 1460</ref>.</note> emphasizing that establishment such
                            services through Saudi Arabia is of course dependent on the rights we
                            hope to obtain. Also state that if agreeable to King we are ready to
                            submit draft bilateral civil air transport agreement similar to those
                            now being negotiated with other countries. Please inform whether we
                            should forward you such draft agreement at this time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>